The paper deals with action detection in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach using a Recurrent Neural Network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Learning). Additionally, the paper involves exploring and searching for actions in videos, which could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with multimedia analysis (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves analyzing untrimmed videos to extract relevant information.
